Hi Folks,

Weâ€™re wondering if anyone has a CAN DBC file, or equivalent format, for the FRC CAN bus? We have mostly CTRE motors and sensors on bot with the Rev PDH. We havenâ€™t tried to snoop on the bus with cantools yet, but would like to.

This has come up as this is the first year weâ€™ve used the SDS swerve modules and associated software release, so we are less familiar with the lower level control parts of our software. Thereâ€™s a regular peak of CAN utilization (nearly 100% for a moment) in the drivers station logs every 250ms that we donâ€™t know the source of. Our previous bots with west coast drive and CTRE PDP had much more stead CAN utilization, but lots has changed since then. Any thoughts on that are also appreciated.

Thanks!

I would also like a CAN database of FRC electronics, however Iâ€™m sure for safety reasons there isnâ€™t one available.

You can probably reduce the utilization of you can bus by modifying how often each message is sent. I know CTRE has some good APIs for limiting the message rate. However, with swerve (8 motors + 4 encoders) Iâ€™m sure itâ€™s very difficult to lower the utilization.

You can also use CTREâ€™s new CANivore which adds CAN FD (3-8x faster/more bandwidth than regular CAN). This will lower your CAN utilization by a lot.

Itâ€™s probably less safety and more wanting to hang onto proprietary info (see: Spark MAX following Talons in 2019). Anyone who knows that the CANbus can be hacked also knows that there are many ways to bypass the disable state or inject their own CAN packets. Having a database file for encoder feedback, for example, would be pretty helpful for low-level debugging at times. Less of a problem now than it was before the REV and Phoenix desktop apps existed.

This thread has some information: SparkMAX following loadless Talon

We appreciate the notes about CANIVORE, though that is slightly orthogonal to the question of understanding what is currently on the bus. Weâ€™ll likely use this in some capacity in the future.

For reference, weâ€™re headed into first comp with a drive base (swerve 8 Falcon + 4 CANcoder) using about 40% utilization plus manipulators (8 more Falcons + 1 CANcoder) adding up to ~75% utilization.

Yes, considering that Rev and CTRE have their desktop apps, I presume it isnâ€™t top of the list to make a unified CAN DBC. Maybe thatâ€™s too be crawled through in the off season. Thanks!

Having competed in EcoCAR in college, Iâ€™ve seen my fair share of CAN DBC files (from GM, MobilEye, etc) and have used my fair share of CAN Bus tools from Kvaser, Vector, etc. These things are usually kept secret because of safety reasons as well as confidentiality.

In EcoCAR, the competition organizers often would install sniffing tools on GMLAN to make sure we werenâ€™t injecting CAN traffic in places that could be seen as a safety hazard.

I wouldnâ€™t expect CTRE, REV, or NI/FIRST to release DBC files. It probably wouldnâ€™t be terribly difficult to decode CAN traffic though, since you have the tools to send known CAN messages.
